<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920114-0116</DOCNO><DOCID>920114-0116.</DOCID><HL>   Westmoreland Coal Co. Unit</HL><DATE>01/14/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   LGE WMOR</CO><MS>ENERGY (ENE)INDUSTRIAL (IDU)UTILITIES (UTI)</MS><IN>COAL PRODUCERS (COA)HEAVY CONSTRUCTION; INDUSTRIAL AND COMMERCIAL (CON)ELECTRIC UTILITIES (ELC)CENTRAL U.S. ELECTRIC UTILITIES (UEC)</IN><NS>FINANCING AGREEMENTS (FNC)</NS><RE>KENTUCKY (KY)NORTH AMERICA (NME)PENNSYLVANIA (PA)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   PHILADELPHIA -- A unit of Westmoreland Coal Co. and a unitof LGandamp;E Energy Corp. said they obtained $300 million infinancing to build a coal-fired power plant.   The plant, to be located near Weldon, N.C., is owned by a50-50 partnership between Westmoreland's Westmoreland EnergyInc. unit and LGandamp;E's LGandamp;E Power Systems Inc.</LP><TEXT>   Westmoreland Energy is a developer and owner ofcogeneration and unregulated power plants. Westmoreland Coal,based in Philadelphia, is a producer of low-sulfur coal. LGandamp;EPower Systems, formerly Hadson Power Systems, develops,builds, operates and owns electric power generationfacilities. LGandamp;E Energy Corp., based in Louisville, Ky., isan energy services company that also owns Louisville Gas andamp;Electric Co.   The financing comes from five financial institutions:Credit Suisse, Prudential Power Funding Associates, NationalWestminster Bank PLC, Bank of Nova Scotia and Sumitomo BankLtd.</TEXT></DOC>